This paper focuses on improving software quality by building test scenarios that resemble the usage of a software product in the field. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNN) to recognize user actions in instructional videos, which falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the potential use of this approach in aiding other software engineering activities that require information about customer usage of a product, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
